Hey there warrior/ warriorettes, just an idea from a longtime nonplaying lurker...didn't even play a warrior so don't h8 me for my suggestion =(<br>
<br>
Been seeing the pain off the warriors out there grow more and more on the messageboards since i stopped playing last year, so rich water's post got me thinking.<br>
<br>
Warriors need a more varied role in regular xp camps, they need a more stackable raiding function...and above all they need to be undisputably the best MT available.<br>
<br>
Well, my proposal is this, give warriors an extra parry attack, but make this parry swing able to parry an attack aimed at ANYONE, as long as the warrior is inside the attack radius of the mob and has the mob in question targeted.<br>
<br>
Give this parry-function a taunt function as well, and off course a chance of success more like kick then normal parrys =)<br>
<br>
As i see it, this would make warriors stackable, a line off warriors could in effect make a a tanking line against a mobb. In the xp group it would add aggro and also give the warrior the ability to save the cleric from that killing blow and so on.<br>
<br>
they would off course need to implement a cap , a point of diminishing returns, as otherwise enough warriors would block all potential blows from a mob...perhaps a penalty such as a guarantied failed double attack the same round would be neccesary. Maybe i'm to far out, it could perhaps just be better to make parry targetable at 60...i don't know, i don't play =)<br>
<br>
